WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:28.529 --> 00:00:31.532
<i>Nothing that's worth anything
comes without pain.</i>

3
00:00:43.543 --> 00:00:46.797
<i>A work of art is only good
if it arises from necessity.</i>

4
00:00:47.464 --> 00:00:48.423
<i>from need.</i>

5
00:00:50.008 --> 00:00:53.303
<i>And it can be political need
or personal need</i>

6
00:00:54.096 --> 00:00:56.139
<i>or. ideally. both.</i>

7
00:00:59.351 --> 00:01:03.105
<i>Art should be confrontation.
It should shock and scare you.</i>

8
00:01:04.690 --> 00:01:05.607
<i>And Hannah.</i>

9
00:01:06.858 --> 00:01:08.485
<i>she was an artist in need.</i>

10
00:01:10.195 --> 00:01:11.780
<i>And I think that's what happened.</i>

11
00:01:12.990 --> 00:01:14.283
<i>And she freaked people out.</i>

12
00:01:14.533 --> 00:01:16.743
All right.

13
00:01:18.579 --> 00:01:24.167
And how does this not make us more likely
to be the targets of abuse and ridicule?

14
00:01:24.876 --> 00:01:28.088
Because it's like claiming the word
as our own.

15
00:01:28.505 --> 00:01:29.798
Reappropriation.

16
00:01:29.881 --> 00:01:32.968
Like saying we're the assholes.
so don't fuck with us.

17
00:01:33.176 --> 00:01:36.388
Okay. yeah. sort of like
our superhero outfits. right?

18
00:01:36.471 --> 00:01:40.851
Like. "It's a bird. it's a plane.
it's the Assholes. It's us."

19
00:01:41.101 --> 00:01:43.562
Yeah. Just maybe don't say that.

20
00:01:53.947 --> 00:01:56.283
<i>A soul in need
needs a way to express it.</i>

21
00:01:57.200 --> 00:01:58.910
<i>Silence is never the answer.</i>

22
00:02:00.162 --> 00:02:02.664
<i>But when there's so much going on
inside you...</i>

23
00:02:05.208 --> 00:02:07.586
<i>...society expects us to stay silent.</i>

24
00:02:16.428 --> 00:02:19.931
<i>And it's a dangerous thing
when there's so much going on inside you.</i>

25
00:02:20.891 --> 00:02:22.434
<i>but no one to share it with.</i>

26
00:02:24.061 --> 00:02:26.730
Kevin? Honey. you forgot your lunch.

27
00:02:27.314 --> 00:02:29.608
- Thanks. I'll be right there.
- Okay.

28
00:02:48.293 --> 00:02:51.213
Good Lord.
These morning practices are killing me.

29
00:02:51.713 --> 00:02:54.341
I'm passing out at exactly 4:30 today.

30
00:02:55.675 --> 00:02:58.512
Or you could come back to my place.

31
00:02:58.762 --> 00:03:00.680
I don't think I'm gonna have the energy...

32
00:03:00.764 --> 00:03:02.724
For dinner? My parents wanna meet you.

33
00:03:02.808 --> 00:03:03.683
- They do?
- Yeah.

34
00:03:03.934 --> 00:03:06.019
That's so cool.

35
00:03:06.103 --> 00:03:08.772
- Oh. my God. that's so terrifying.
- No. It's no big deal.

36
00:03:08.855 --> 00:03:10.732
My dad happens to be in town for a bit.

37
00:03:11.900 --> 00:03:13.485
I'm always talking about you.

38
00:03:13.693 --> 00:03:16.655
I'm so excited. Amazing.

39
00:03:16.863 --> 00:03:18.240
- See you in third.
- Okay. Bye.

40
00:03:21.993 --> 00:03:23.495
Babe. I wanted to talk to you about...

41
00:03:23.578 --> 00:03:25.205
Wait. I should buy a dress.

42
00:03:25.414 --> 00:03:27.749
- You don't need to buy a dress.
- Or at least go and change.

43
00:03:27.833 --> 00:03:30.669
- I'll need at least an hour. okay?
- Yeah. fine.

44
00:03:30.877 --> 00:03:32.629
Hey. uh. how is practice

45
00:03:32.712 --> 00:03:36.091
with all the captain stuff
and. you know. Jess?

46
00:03:36.425 --> 00:03:38.301
It's great. It's going really well.

47
00:03:38.552 --> 00:03:40.011
Cool. Awesome. Okay.

48
00:03:40.095 --> 00:03:41.054
- Bye.
- Bye.

49
00:03:42.556 --> 00:03:44.599
<i>Hannah needed
to reclaim her power.</i>

50
00:03:45.517 --> 00:03:47.185
Are you gonna ask him about the Polaroid?

51
00:03:48.145 --> 00:03:50.188
I don't trust him any more
than I did yesterday.

52
00:03:50.272 --> 00:03:53.692
How can you not trust
that little sleeping angel?

53
00:04:00.991 --> 00:04:02.409
The fuck are you looking at?

54
00:04:04.161 --> 00:04:07.205
Justin. do you think
that you can keep your shit together

55
00:04:07.289 --> 00:04:09.958
until someone comes over
to look after you later?

56
00:04:10.417 --> 00:04:12.335
I'm running late. I gotta get to school.

57
00:04:12.461 --> 00:04:15.338
I'm fine. I don't need a babysitter.

58
00:04:16.590 --> 00:04:18.467
It's just so fucking cold in here.

59
00:04:18.800 --> 00:04:21.553
- Chills. He has a fever.
- It's chills. You have a fever.

60
00:04:21.636 --> 00:04:23.180
Well. get him another blanket.

61
00:04:32.564 --> 00:04:35.025
- Maybe a shower would help.
- I'm not that bad.

62
00:04:35.108 --> 00:04:38.445
You smell like dead feet.
Just shower. please.

63
00:04:38.945 --> 00:04:39.946
Oh. I'm hungry.

64
00:04:41.239 --> 00:04:43.492
How can you be hungry?
You threw everything up.

65
00:04:45.285 --> 00:04:46.536
Maybe that's why I'm hungry.

66
00:04:48.789 --> 00:04:49.706
Take a shower.

67
00:04:52.167 --> 00:04:53.168
Have you seen this?

68
00:04:54.669 --> 00:04:58.757
My God. was there anyone in your class
this Hannah wasn't involved with?

69
00:05:00.050 --> 00:05:01.259
What? What do you mean?

70
00:05:01.426 --> 00:05:03.678
Every day.
there's another boy in this story.

71
00:05:05.722 --> 00:05:08.141
It's not surprising
that she had a reputation.

72
00:05:10.143 --> 00:05:13.563
I will just be glad
when this is all over for you tomorrow.

73
00:05:14.022 --> 00:05:17.067
and you are as far removed
from this mess as possible.

74
00:05:19.194 --> 00:05:20.070
Yep.

75
00:05:33.959 --> 00:05:36.628
Hey. Your mom's starting to think
you're avoiding us.

76
00:05:37.045 --> 00:05:40.966
Avoiding you? No. No. no.
I've just got a lot going on. you know?

77
00:05:41.049 --> 00:05:42.884
You can't take every meal in your room.

78
00:05:44.219 --> 00:05:47.430
I've just got so much work.

79
00:05:47.889 --> 00:05:51.393
How about taking a break with me tonight?
<i>Vertigo</i> is at the Crestmont.

80
00:05:51.476 --> 00:05:52.394
Let's go.

81
00:05:53.645 --> 00:05:55.272
Oh. wow. I. um...

82
00:05:56.439 --> 00:05:57.941
Is that the shower?

83
00:05:58.024 --> 00:06:00.026
Yeah. Yeah. that's my. um...

84
00:06:00.485 --> 00:06:02.988
I just figured I'd grab some food
while I let it heat up.

85
00:06:03.071 --> 00:06:05.115
The new tankless heater
takes a while to warm up.

86
00:06:05.198 --> 00:06:07.242
- Shouldn't take this long.
- It's not a big deal.

87
00:06:07.325 --> 00:06:09.953
No. sometimes the valve
is on the cold side.

88
00:06:10.036 --> 00:06:11.329
It's all good. Have some coffee.

89
00:06:12.414 --> 00:06:14.165
Yeah. I'll get more. Yeah. Movie tonight?

90
00:06:14.708 --> 00:06:16.960
Exciting. So. yeah. thanks.

91
00:06:25.844 --> 00:06:27.012
What the fuck?

92
00:06:27.095 --> 00:06:30.265
Yeah. Dad. Plenty hot.
Water heater's totally working.

93
00:06:34.603 --> 00:06:36.396
- Shit. Sorry.
- Just quiet.

94
00:06:36.479 --> 00:06:37.564
Okay.

95
00:06:45.238 --> 00:06:46.323
Can you get out now?

96
00:06:46.865 --> 00:06:49.075
It has to look like
I'm the one in the shower. idiot.

97
00:06:51.328 --> 00:06:54.456
Well. can you pass me some more shampoo?

98
00:06:55.707 --> 00:06:57.417
These kids need to be sympathetic. Olivia.

99
00:06:57.500 --> 00:07:00.837
I worry about calling Ryan Shaver.
His deposition was practically smug.

100
00:07:00.920 --> 00:07:03.923
We're putting pieces together. We have to
get Hannah's poem into evidence.

101
00:07:04.007 --> 00:07:05.258
and he's the one who...

102
00:07:06.718 --> 00:07:07.552
printed it.

103
00:07:10.805 --> 00:07:11.640
Morning.

104
00:07:12.724 --> 00:07:14.893
- Hi. I'm Andy.
- Oh. of course. I remember.

105
00:07:15.685 --> 00:07:17.646
- Will you be joining us today?
- No. he won't.

106
00:07:20.106 --> 00:07:22.067
Well. I'll give you two a minute.

107
00:07:27.447 --> 00:07:29.199
I wanna be here with you.

108
00:07:29.783 --> 00:07:33.036
I need to be here.
I'm sorry I haven't been.

109
00:07:33.787 --> 00:07:35.580
The things they've been saying in there.

110
00:07:36.456 --> 00:07:40.293
things that you'll hear. you have no idea.

111
00:07:41.711 --> 00:07:42.545
I'll learn.

112
00:07:47.217 --> 00:07:51.054
I don't know.
It's definitely not the pool house.

113
00:07:52.639 --> 00:07:54.182
So. where is it. then?

114
00:07:54.683 --> 00:07:57.811
I could ask one of the guys
and maybe figure out...

115
00:07:57.894 --> 00:08:02.774
No. You stay here
until you're clean. For Jessica.

116
00:08:04.317 --> 00:08:06.069
I could just show this around. It's...

117
00:08:06.653 --> 00:08:07.904
No. I got it. Thanks.

118
00:08:08.488 --> 00:08:09.990
Fuck me. Fuck.

119
00:08:12.492 --> 00:08:13.535
Wait...

120
00:08:14.327 --> 00:08:16.579
He's my babysitter?
What happened to Sheri?

121
00:08:16.871 --> 00:08:20.625
Sheri couldn't skip twice in a row.
She's taking the evening shift.

122
00:08:21.251 --> 00:08:23.128
I thought he wanted nothing to do with me.

123
00:08:23.420 --> 00:08:24.337
No. I don't.

124
00:08:24.713 --> 00:08:27.132
So keep your mouth shut
and don't piss me off.

125
00:08:27.215 --> 00:08:29.009
Don't piss <i>me </i>off.

126
00:08:29.092 --> 00:08:32.053
And if you puke on this leather.
I'm gonna have to kick your ass.

127
00:08:32.303 --> 00:08:33.138
Great.

128
00:08:33.722 --> 00:08:38.601
So. WebMD detox info and contingency plans
are on the desk.

129
00:08:38.685 --> 00:08:42.355
Don't let anyone see you. And I gotta go.

130
00:08:42.439 --> 00:08:45.817
Um. have fun.
Don't kill each other. Thanks.

131
00:08:46.651 --> 00:08:47.610
Bye.

132
00:08:49.529 --> 00:08:51.573
<i>But. as is almost always the case
in high school.</i>

133
00:08:51.656 --> 00:08:53.491
<i>we mock what we don't understand.</i>

134
00:08:53.575 --> 00:08:55.326
That's what kids at Liberty did to Hannah.

135
00:08:55.410 --> 00:08:56.494
What about faculty?

136
00:08:56.619 --> 00:09:00.749
I mean. didn't they express concern
over the poem's suicidal contents?

137
00:09:00.874 --> 00:09:04.294
The poem was read aloud
in Mrs. Cusick's class. That's about it.

138
00:09:04.586 --> 00:09:06.212
So no one addressed

139
00:09:06.296 --> 00:09:09.758
the anonymous author's
obvious cry for help

140
00:09:09.841 --> 00:09:12.427
or asked you who wrote it?

141
00:09:12.719 --> 00:09:14.304
Nope. No one took it seriously.

142
00:09:15.847 --> 00:09:17.474
But then again. they rarely do.

143
00:09:36.868 --> 00:09:37.869
Mr. Down?

144
00:09:42.749 --> 00:09:44.709
My office. now.

145
00:09:59.307 --> 00:10:00.767
I think you know why you're here.

146
00:10:01.434 --> 00:10:02.268
Yeah. I'm aware.

147
00:10:09.150 --> 00:10:10.610
You wanna tell me about these?

148
00:10:12.403 --> 00:10:14.072
Wait. that's what this is about?

149
00:10:14.656 --> 00:10:16.199
You took the pictures.

150
00:10:17.117 --> 00:10:19.119
Yeah. last year.

151
00:10:20.286 --> 00:10:22.455
How'd they end up saying. "drunk slut"?

152
00:10:23.123 --> 00:10:24.707
Mr. Porter. I didn't do that.

153
00:10:25.041 --> 00:10:27.085
I went into the photography classroom.

154
00:10:27.168 --> 00:10:30.088
and the printer history in the lab
said that <i>you </i>were signed in.

155
00:10:30.296 --> 00:10:33.550
Someone must've used it while
I was developing in the darkroom then.

156
00:10:33.633 --> 00:10:34.467
Okay.

157
00:10:35.844 --> 00:10:38.930
So do we know who might be doing this
to Jessica. then?

158
00:10:39.848 --> 00:10:43.017
Same person who smashed my camera.
Did anyone ever find them?

159
00:10:43.977 --> 00:10:45.728
But Jessica and I get messed with?

160
00:10:46.020 --> 00:10:48.231
And the people that deserve
to get messed with never do.

161
00:10:48.606 --> 00:10:49.858
I think that can change.

162
00:10:50.024 --> 00:10:51.568
I'll believe it when I see it.

163
00:11:06.166 --> 00:11:09.460
Isn't this. like.
your special resources period?

164
00:11:09.836 --> 00:11:13.423
Yeah. I hate that shit.
I just... I gotta listen to these again.

165
00:11:15.925 --> 00:11:16.968
Alex. uh...

166
00:11:20.263 --> 00:11:22.640
last time. you listened.
I think. multiple times.

167
00:11:22.724 --> 00:11:24.183
Yeah. I know. I just...

168
00:11:25.059 --> 00:11:28.271
I keep listening to mine over and over
because it doesn't make sense.

169
00:11:29.272 --> 00:11:30.732
It's like I'm missing something.

170
00:11:33.192 --> 00:11:34.068
Do you...

171
00:11:35.069 --> 00:11:36.195
Do you wanna talk about it?

172
00:11:36.863 --> 00:11:39.407
- Aren't we talking about it?
- I guess so.

173
00:11:46.372 --> 00:11:47.999
Hey. what is that guy doing?

174
00:11:48.374 --> 00:11:50.043
Uh. chalking the field.

175
00:11:51.169 --> 00:11:52.045
What is that machine?

176
00:11:52.503 --> 00:11:55.506
I don't know.
Like... I guess it's a chalk machine?

177
00:11:56.966 --> 00:11:57.800
I gotta go.

178
00:11:58.051 --> 00:12:00.011
I don't know
if it's called a chalk machine.

179
00:12:00.094 --> 00:12:01.179
No. I just...

180
00:12:02.472 --> 00:12:05.934
- Look. don't listen too hard. okay?
- Yeah.

181
00:12:25.453 --> 00:12:28.331
<i>It seems like nothing
until the hurricane hits.</i>

182
00:12:29.123 --> 00:12:30.375
<i>Is that why you did it. Alex?</i>

183
00:12:36.673 --> 00:12:39.384
<i>I can't pretend to know
what goes on in someone else's head.</i>

184
00:12:39.801 --> 00:12:41.010
It's poetry.

185
00:12:41.094 --> 00:12:44.013
Most of the poets in our group
write about dark and messed-up things.

186
00:12:44.097 --> 00:12:48.601
So you had no idea that Hannah
was crying out for help in her work.

187
00:12:48.685 --> 00:12:50.687
or so the prosecution
would have us believe.

188
00:12:50.770 --> 00:12:53.898
but you expect the school
to draw that conclusion?

189
00:12:53.982 --> 00:12:55.566
It's their job. isn't it?

190
00:12:56.401 --> 00:12:58.861
I mean. I'm sorry.
but I'm not a licensed therapist.

191
00:12:58.945 --> 00:12:59.862
or a teacher.

192
00:13:00.279 --> 00:13:03.324
Ryan. isn't it true that you worked
with Hannah

193
00:13:03.408 --> 00:13:05.118
on many of her other poems?

194
00:13:05.660 --> 00:13:07.328
Some. yes.

195
00:13:08.288 --> 00:13:10.832
And do you recognize these?

196
00:13:16.921 --> 00:13:19.465
Yes. they're other poems
from Hannah's journals.

197
00:13:19.757 --> 00:13:21.592
Defense Exhibit F. Your Honor.

198
00:13:21.676 --> 00:13:24.637
Uh. Ryan. did you work with Hannah
on this poem?

199
00:13:25.138 --> 00:13:26.305
Yes. I did.

200
00:13:27.181 --> 00:13:29.225
Would you read this poem
for the court. please?

201
00:13:36.566 --> 00:13:39.277
"Oh. fruit forbidden.
so sour. so sweet..."

202
00:13:39.569 --> 00:13:41.487
"I have been banished from the garden.

203
00:13:41.571 --> 00:13:42.864
and I don't think I miss it.

204
00:13:43.656 --> 00:13:45.575
And yet I want another bite."

205
00:13:48.578 --> 00:13:50.747
I like how you subverted the ode.
That's good.

206
00:13:52.040 --> 00:13:53.916
Some obvious metaphors there.

207
00:13:55.334 --> 00:13:57.211
but there's a universality to it.

208
00:13:58.671 --> 00:13:59.922
I'm just...

209
00:14:01.507 --> 00:14:02.675
Sorry. uh. keep going.

210
00:14:03.384 --> 00:14:07.013
I was going to say. I'm just wondering
if you shouldn't delve a little deeper.

211
00:14:07.388 --> 00:14:08.806
You had another you wanted to read?

212
00:14:08.890 --> 00:14:09.766
Uh...

213
00:14:09.849 --> 00:14:11.017
- Yeah.
- Okay.

214
00:14:11.100 --> 00:14:14.979
Look. I know it seems silly.
but the no-phone rule is for a very good...

215
00:14:19.817 --> 00:14:21.235
Justin Foley?

216
00:14:23.237 --> 00:14:24.447
Shut up. Are...?

217
00:14:26.991 --> 00:14:27.909
Hang on.

218
00:14:28.743 --> 00:14:30.536
Holy shit.

219
00:14:30.620 --> 00:14:32.747
- He's your forbidden fruit?
- No. he's not.

220
00:14:32.830 --> 00:14:34.999
- We just text sometimes.
- Oh. you text?

221
00:14:35.375 --> 00:14:37.377
And talk on the phone a little.

222
00:14:37.543 --> 00:14:39.295
- Since when?
- I don't know.

223
00:14:39.379 --> 00:14:41.672
He texted me that day saying he was sorry.

224
00:14:41.756 --> 00:14:44.801
and then. again. the next day.
Eventually. I stopped ignoring him.

225
00:14:45.301 --> 00:14:48.054
And it felt good to know that things
didn't end up the way

226
00:14:48.137 --> 00:14:50.014
- that people think they did.
- What...?

227
00:14:50.640 --> 00:14:53.476
- You just told me to delve deeper.
- Not into him.

228
00:14:53.643 --> 00:14:55.853
- You said yourself he ruined you.
- I know.

229
00:14:56.646 --> 00:14:59.107
- I know. I just...
- Okay. I get it.

230
00:14:59.774 --> 00:15:01.067
He makes all our panties drop.

231
00:15:01.567 --> 00:15:03.277
Wait. you think Justin's hot?

232
00:15:03.361 --> 00:15:06.489
Of course I do. I'm not blind.
or. like. chemically castrated.

233
00:15:06.823 --> 00:15:08.533
You said. and I'm quoting.

234
00:15:08.616 --> 00:15:11.953
that he was "the exemplar
of athleticus douchebaggerus."

235
00:15:12.036 --> 00:15:13.579
Which only makes him hotter.

236
00:15:13.830 --> 00:15:16.833
- I know. right? How is that even fair?
- All right. enough.

237
00:15:17.375 --> 00:15:20.211
You put your hand on the hot stove.
Owie! You've learned your lesson.

238
00:15:21.379 --> 00:15:23.047
- Yes?
- Yes.

239
00:15:26.342 --> 00:15:28.469
You are going to delete him
from your phone...

240
00:15:28.553 --> 00:15:30.680
- Ugh.
- ...and cleanse him from your heart.

241
00:15:30.763 --> 00:15:33.266
Well. we should probably skip
my next three poems.

242
00:15:33.933 --> 00:15:35.268
Why?

243
00:15:39.939 --> 00:15:41.357
