Okay?

498
00:31:02.486 --> 00:31:07.240
The last thing I need in my life right now
is some fucking guy.

499
00:31:07.908 --> 00:31:11.119
And you. the fact that you keep.
like. offering that...

500
00:31:12.704 --> 00:31:15.207
means you're just as fucking clueless
as I thought.

501
00:31:24.716 --> 00:31:26.468
<i>I was trying
to be Hannah's friend.</i>

502
00:31:27.552 --> 00:31:29.888
<i>I needed a friend as much as she did.</i>

503
00:31:33.058 --> 00:31:35.060
Um. Hi.

504
00:31:37.229 --> 00:31:38.063
Hi.

505
00:31:38.146 --> 00:31:38.980
I. um...

506
00:31:40.065 --> 00:31:43.151
I was friends with Hannah.
and I let her down. and I'm sorry.

507
00:31:43.735 --> 00:31:46.696
I just wanted to come by and say
what they're doing to her is bullshit.

508
00:31:49.282 --> 00:31:50.117
Thank you.

509
00:31:52.160 --> 00:31:53.161
Can I...?

510
00:31:55.872 --> 00:31:58.291
Can I ask you some questions
about Hannah's journals?

511
00:32:00.085 --> 00:32:00.919
Oh. um...

512
00:32:03.672 --> 00:32:05.215
Yes. of course.

513
00:32:14.433 --> 00:32:17.936
She mentions "the clubhouse"
in three different poems.

514
00:32:19.646 --> 00:32:22.315
"Something changed after the clubhouse.

515
00:32:23.775 --> 00:32:25.861
I imagined myself for a moment
one of the elite.

516
00:32:25.944 --> 00:32:28.363
but I never should have gone
to the clubhouse."

517
00:32:28.572 --> 00:32:30.365
"...in his lucky letter jacket."

518
00:32:30.449 --> 00:32:33.910
- That's gotta be Justin. right?
- It could be.

519
00:32:34.661 --> 00:32:35.495
I don't know.

520
00:32:36.913 --> 00:32:38.748
I don't remember anything
about a clubhouse.

521
00:32:38.832 --> 00:32:39.666
Damn it.

522
00:32:40.584 --> 00:32:44.129
Okay. What about "the intruder"?

523
00:32:45.213 --> 00:32:49.009
He comes up several times. too.
There's a whole poem about him.

524
00:32:49.426 --> 00:32:52.262
"Sometimes the intruder
doesn't need to break a window.

525
00:32:52.637 --> 00:32:54.598
Sometimes they already have the key."

526
00:32:55.432 --> 00:32:56.516
Do you know this one?

527
00:32:57.434 --> 00:32:58.268
No.

528
00:32:59.978 --> 00:33:01.938
I think it's about the bullying
at the school.

529
00:33:03.315 --> 00:33:04.733
The house is on fire.

530
00:33:05.567 --> 00:33:07.277
her lungs are filling up with smoke.

531
00:33:07.360 --> 00:33:08.778
and the intruder.

532
00:33:09.112 --> 00:33:12.449
it's this other Hannah
that everyone thought they knew.

533
00:33:12.532 --> 00:33:13.909
Oh. no. that makes sense.

534
00:33:23.502 --> 00:33:24.961
It's fucking useless. Ryan.

535
00:33:25.295 --> 00:33:29.174
We write and write about shit.
and nothing ever changes. I'm done.

536
00:33:29.591 --> 00:33:32.344
Hannah. you have a gift.
Not gonna let you throw that away.

537
00:33:32.844 --> 00:33:33.678
A gift?

538
00:33:34.262 --> 00:33:37.098
- You say that so easily like you know.
- I do.

539
00:33:37.182 --> 00:33:38.517
Yeah. well. I wish <i>I </i>did.

540
00:33:39.267 --> 00:33:41.228
I wish I didn't need people
to tell me I'm good.

541
00:33:41.311 --> 00:33:43.772
or that they like me. but I do.

542
00:33:44.272 --> 00:33:47.234
That... That's great stuff.
That's what you should write about.

543
00:33:47.317 --> 00:33:48.151
No.

544
00:33:48.235 --> 00:33:50.946
Enough writing about my emotions.
Can we just eat them?

545
00:33:51.029 --> 00:33:53.532
Yeah. we can totally eat them.

546
00:33:55.617 --> 00:33:57.827
Vanilla or mint chocolate chip?

547
00:33:58.370 --> 00:34:01.331
Please. Vanilla is not a flavor.
It's an admission of defeat.

548
00:34:08.380 --> 00:34:11.675
<i>Hannah was so talented.
but she didn't know it.</i>

549
00:34:13.718 --> 00:34:15.845
<i>She wrote out of love. out of need.</i>

550
00:34:20.850 --> 00:34:23.770
<i>And I wanted to show her
that the rush of people loving your work</i>

551
00:34:23.853 --> 00:34:25.272
<i>is just as good as love.</i>

552
00:34:38.952 --> 00:34:40.537
<i>It was just one poem.</i>

553
00:34:48.878 --> 00:34:49.713
<i>But I was wrong.</i>

554
00:34:50.547 --> 00:34:52.549
I'm sorry I can't be more helpful.

555
00:34:54.718 --> 00:35:01.182
Sometimes I fantasize that all the answers
are in these torn-out pages.

556
00:35:01.641 --> 00:35:04.436
Oh. I... I don't think so. I...

557
00:35:06.521 --> 00:35:08.690
I imagine those are just
false starts or...

558
00:35:09.816 --> 00:35:13.403
things she was ashamed
to even admit to herself.

559
00:35:14.321 --> 00:35:16.573
Why did she keep in contact with Justin?

560
00:35:17.407 --> 00:35:18.325
Loneliness.

561
00:35:20.410 --> 00:35:21.995
It can be intense at our age.

562
00:35:23.038 --> 00:35:24.414
It's not just at your age.

563
00:35:30.962 --> 00:35:32.839
<i>What she needed most was love.</i>

564
00:35:33.882 --> 00:35:34.883
<i>Human connection.</i>

565
00:36:02.786 --> 00:36:07.207
You didn't quit cheerleading
because Justin's back?

566
00:36:10.460 --> 00:36:12.545
I know. news travels fast in these halls.

567
00:36:13.380 --> 00:36:14.255
Don't care.

568
00:36:14.464 --> 00:36:16.508
- You don't care that he's back?
- No.

569
00:36:16.800 --> 00:36:17.884
Know where he's staying?

570
00:36:21.304 --> 00:36:22.597
Justin needs help. too.

571
00:36:24.265 --> 00:36:26.017
He should be enrolled in school.

572
00:36:26.393 --> 00:36:30.146
The only address I have of him
is his dad in Sacramento.

573
00:36:32.982 --> 00:36:33.817
Oh. well.

574
00:36:34.484 --> 00:36:36.903
Jess. I'll be honest.

575
00:36:38.780 --> 00:36:42.325
I know what it's like to try to be strong

576
00:36:43.076 --> 00:36:44.828
and keep your problems all to you.

577
00:36:45.787 --> 00:36:46.871
But it does not work.

578
00:36:49.582 --> 00:36:51.000
You don't have to talk to me.

579
00:36:53.461 --> 00:36:55.004
But talk to someone.

580
00:36:56.089 --> 00:36:58.091
If I don't have to talk to you. can I go?

581
00:37:07.142 --> 00:37:08.518
Justin's never met his dad.

582
00:37:10.145 --> 00:37:12.605
His mom lives with some drug dealer
named Seth.

583
00:37:28.121 --> 00:37:30.081
- Do you think she likes her?
- Your mother?

584
00:37:30.165 --> 00:37:31.541
- Yeah.
- Uh. sure.

585
00:37:35.003 --> 00:37:36.921
Chlöe's a great girl. Very pretty.

586
00:37:37.338 --> 00:37:40.467
Yeah. she's got a brain. too.
Her grades are better than mine.

587
00:37:42.218 --> 00:37:43.094
And she's loyal?

588
00:37:44.804 --> 00:37:45.722
Yeah.

589
00:37:47.098 --> 00:37:48.183
That's important.

590
00:37:48.558 --> 00:37:51.060
- You did good.
- Thanks. Dad.

591
00:37:52.687 --> 00:37:53.605
Here we go.

592
00:37:55.356 --> 00:37:56.274
Wow.

593
00:37:57.567 --> 00:37:59.819
You seem quite happy. the two of you.

594
00:37:59.903 --> 00:38:03.948
Oh. yeah. absolutely.
He's so sweet to me. like. all the time.

595
00:38:04.032 --> 00:38:05.200
- Sweet?
- Yeah.

596
00:38:05.909 --> 00:38:07.827
That's good to hear.

597
00:38:17.003 --> 00:38:19.464
Oh. Cheerleading. Full-contact sport.

598
00:38:20.882 --> 00:38:21.883
I see.

599
00:38:26.012 --> 00:38:27.222
How do you know about Justin?

600
00:38:27.847 --> 00:38:30.558
Because Jessica told me
when we ditched with your car yesterday.

601
00:38:31.476 --> 00:38:32.936
Said that Clay went and found him.

602
00:38:33.770 --> 00:38:34.938
- Clay?
- Yeah.

603
00:38:36.231 --> 00:38:39.651
Okay. do you know anything about
where he's living or why he's back?

604
00:38:39.734 --> 00:38:42.362
No. Zach. and I really don't fucking care.

605
00:38:42.445 --> 00:38:44.614
Why is everything always
about fucking Justin?

606
00:38:44.697 --> 00:38:47.659
Whoa. Relax. dude. It's not.

607
00:38:49.536 --> 00:38:52.956
- Hey. are you okay?
- Yeah.

608
00:38:53.414 --> 00:38:55.083
Jessica and I kissed yesterday.

609
00:38:56.584 --> 00:38:57.502
Seriously?

610
00:38:57.961 --> 00:38:59.712
Dude. that's... that's great.

611
00:39:01.214 --> 00:39:02.048
Is that great?

612
00:39:02.966 --> 00:39:05.218
Yeah. well.
but then she freaked out on me.

613
00:39:06.386 --> 00:39:08.638
And now it's just...
It's totally weird. I...

614
00:39:10.390 --> 00:39:12.809
Yeah. that makes sense
that she would freak out.

615
00:39:13.601 --> 00:39:17.188
Yeah. But I just... I still think
it has something to do with Justin.

616
00:39:18.231 --> 00:39:20.149
And you know what's the most fucked up?

617
00:39:21.442 --> 00:39:23.820
When we kissed.
I couldn't even feel anything.

618
00:39:25.613 --> 00:39:29.200
- You mean. like. emotionally. or...?
- No. like. down there.

619
00:39:29.909 --> 00:39:30.952
I was just numb.

620
00:39:32.996 --> 00:39:35.665
I haven't really felt anything.
like. post-coma.

621
00:39:36.875 --> 00:39:39.669
- Have you tried porn?
- Yeah. of course I've tried porn.

622
00:39:39.752 --> 00:39:42.297
But I thought with a real person.
maybe it would. you know.

623
00:39:43.548 --> 00:39:48.219
Yeah. Well. dude. honestly. it'll happen.
You just gotta find the right girl.

624
00:39:48.803 --> 00:39:49.804
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

625
00:39:50.305 --> 00:39:52.515
All right. well. let me know
when you find yours.

626
00:39:53.558 --> 00:39:56.436
Maybe she's got a friend
who's into scrawny and broken.

627
00:39:57.604 --> 00:39:59.063
Well. not broken forever.

628
00:40:00.273 --> 00:40:01.232
Let's go. Come on.

629
00:40:07.030 --> 00:40:08.406
<i>I'm sorry. Sheri.</i>

630
00:40:08.573 --> 00:40:10.742
He went to the movies with his dad.

631
00:40:11.492 --> 00:40:15.747
- He must have forgotten to text you.
- Yeah. he must have.

632
00:40:16.831 --> 00:40:21.544
I'm happy that you two are friends again.
I know you've been through a great deal.

633
00:40:21.920 --> 00:40:23.379
Yeah. we have.

634
00:40:23.922 --> 00:40:26.382
I think Clay's still working
on trying to forgive me.

635
00:40:26.925 --> 00:40:30.178
- Well. if he asked you to come study...
- Yeah.

636
00:40:30.762 --> 00:40:33.139
Actually. why don't you stay?
Wait for him.

637
00:40:33.973 --> 00:40:34.807
Sure.

638
00:40:40.188 --> 00:40:42.899
Can I ask you a question
for a case that I'm working on?

639
00:40:44.901 --> 00:40:49.197
Let's say a boy and a girl. uh.
have been texting a lot.

640
00:40:49.781 --> 00:40:53.618
and then all of a sudden. it stops.
what would that mean?

641
00:40:54.410 --> 00:40:57.497
Well. they were probably dating. right?
Then they broke up.

642
00:40:57.580 --> 00:40:58.873
What if they never dated?

643
00:40:59.207 --> 00:41:02.043
Oh. That's probably just a hookup.

644
00:41:04.003 --> 00:41:06.631
<i>Hannah was desperate
for human connection.</i>

645
00:41:06.923 --> 00:41:08.508
<i>and I betrayed her.</i>

646
00:41:12.011 --> 00:41:14.764
<i>I guess I left her even more lonely
than she was before.</i>

647
00:41:19.644 --> 00:41:21.437
<i>And I guess I know how she feels.</i>

648
00:41:41.749 --> 00:41:42.792
How'd it go today?

649
00:41:42.917 --> 00:41:45.920
Um. Not great. actually.

650
00:41:46.421 --> 00:41:48.589
You're fine.
I didn't say anything. if you're worried.

651
00:41:48.673 --> 00:41:52.593
I wasn't. I... just wanted to know
how you were doing.

652
00:41:53.970 --> 00:41:54.887
Are you here alone?

653
00:41:56.764 --> 00:41:58.891
- You wanna join us?
- "Us"?

654
00:42:00.268 --> 00:42:03.104
Caleb. Ryan. Ryan. Caleb.

655
00:42:03.521 --> 00:42:05.440
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice...

656
00:42:06.607 --> 00:42:08.317
handshake. wow.

657
00:42:08.985 --> 00:42:10.945
Sure you don't wanna join us?

658
00:42:12.280 --> 00:42:14.907
Yeah. actually. no. I was just leaving.
I got stood up.

659
00:42:15.033 --> 00:42:18.578
Apparently. my date joined the app today.
He's a noob. so you know. Just...

660
00:42:18.911 --> 00:42:19.746
Um...

661
00:42:19.954 --> 00:42:23.458
Forget him. Stay.
Plus I want some dirt on Mr. Perfect here.

662
00:42:23.750 --> 00:42:26.711
- Oh. he knows about our past. that's...
- Barely any of it.

663
00:42:27.295 --> 00:42:29.422
You're not interested
in high school bullshit.

664
00:42:29.505 --> 00:42:31.758
If it's about you. I am.

665
00:42:32.800 --> 00:42:35.845
Come on. Ryan. Seriously. Stay.

666
00:42:38.890 --> 00:42:42.477
<i>What Hannah needed was a friend.
and I wasn't that.</i>

667
00:42:44.854 --> 00:42:48.274
For the longest time.
nothing was the same.

668
00:42:49.233 --> 00:42:52.779
How long I slept. what I ate. what I wore.

669
00:42:55.114 --> 00:42:57.283
I mean. my clothes
didn't feel like me anymore.

670
00:42:57.784 --> 00:42:59.535
Bright colors made me feel like a fraud

671
00:42:59.619 --> 00:43:01.954
and my black clothes
didn't seem dark enough. and...

672
00:43:02.205 --> 00:43:05.792
Just nothing seemed to fit.
Just literally everything felt like a lie.

673
00:43:07.126 --> 00:43:10.755
And nothing I did seemed to help.
No drink. no drug.

674
00:43:12.381 --> 00:43:15.468
Well. I didn't actually try every drug.

675
00:43:15.551 --> 00:43:18.888
but let me tell you. weed just had me
crying and all in my feelings.

676
00:43:19.972 --> 00:43:22.934
You know. but the one thing
that did seem to help was all of you.

677
00:43:24.268 --> 00:43:25.853
And I'm thankful today that just...

678
00:43:27.063 --> 00:43:28.397
coming here and talking to you

679
00:43:28.481 --> 00:43:30.942
has been the thing
that's brought me back to who I am.

680
00:43:32.318 --> 00:43:34.987
You know. a loud. pushy. pain in the ass.

681
00:43:37.740 --> 00:43:40.409
But you know you love me. and I love you.

682
00:43:42.620 --> 00:43:43.579
Thank you.

683
00:43:50.211 --> 00:43:51.254
Took you long enough.

684
00:43:55.007 --> 00:43:56.008
How did you know?

685
00:43:57.260 --> 00:43:58.261
About me.

686
00:43:58.636 --> 00:44:01.055
Um. I didn't.

687
00:44:01.639 --> 00:44:03.891
I just figured in case
those rumors were bullshit.

688
00:44:03.975 --> 00:44:06.269
which they obviously were.
that I'd be a friendly face.

689
00:44:07.436 --> 00:44:11.065
Friendly and slightly stalkerish?

690
00:44:11.482 --> 00:44:13.359
I don't stalk. I lurk.

691
00:44:13.442 --> 00:44:15.778
- Oh. okay.
- And it worked. didn't it?

692
00:44:18.656 --> 00:44:20.199
Yeah.

693
00:44:26.706 --> 00:44:28.291
Honey?

694
00:44:34.547 --> 00:44:35.715
Turn it down.

695
00:44:36.340 --> 00:44:38.176
- What?
- Turn the music down.

696
00:44:41.804 --> 00:44:43.055
Hey. sorry. what?

697
00:44:43.472 --> 00:44:44.849
That's. um...

698
00:44:46.434 --> 00:44:47.935
some music.

699
00:44:48.811 --> 00:44:50.521
- It's punk.
- Oh.

700
00:44:52.857 --> 00:44:54.775
They sound angry.

701
00:44:54.942 --> 00:44:56.402
- They are.
- Oh.

702
00:44:57.570 --> 00:44:59.530
Okay. Uh...

703
00:45:01.365 --> 00:45:02.950
What are they so angry about?

704
00:45:04.452 --> 00:45:05.453
Everything.

705
00:45:06.996 --> 00:45:08.247
- I see.
- Yeah.

706
00:45:12.376 --> 00:45:15.421
Mr. Barbour called today.
From up the street.

707
00:45:16.297 --> 00:45:20.676
He said he saw you and your friend. Cyrus.
shooting guns on his property.

708
00:45:21.260 --> 00:45:24.221
What? Shooting guns?

709
00:45:25.723 --> 00:45:28.684
That wasn't me. I don't know. I...

710
00:45:28.768 --> 00:45:30.686
- That old guy's crazy. I guess.
- No.

711
00:45:31.062 --> 00:45:34.357
He said it was you. That's why
he called me and not the police.

712
00:45:37.944 --> 00:45:41.739
Oh. wait. does he mean...
does he mean Cyrus' BB gun?

713
00:45:42.448 --> 00:45:45.242
- Is that what he's talking about?
- A BB gun?

714
00:45:45.326 --> 00:45:48.579
It's like this old thing Cyrus has.
It's like a toy.

715
00:45:49.080 --> 00:45:50.206
You know. it's not real.

716
00:45:50.665 --> 00:45:53.250
- Maybe that's what he saw.
- Oh. Okay.

717
00:45:54.168 --> 00:45:55.044
Hmm.

718
00:45:55.127 --> 00:45:57.672
Still. you know how I feel
about guns of any kind.

719
00:45:57.755 --> 00:46:00.758
Yeah. No. I do. I do.
And I even... I told Cyrus that.

720
00:46:00.841 --> 00:46:03.803
Which is why we went to
Mr. Barbour's field to be extra careful.

721
00:46:04.261 --> 00:46:06.430
And did Cyrus give you that music?

722
00:46:07.139 --> 00:46:08.182
And that shirt?

723
00:46:09.850 --> 00:46:13.229
We made the shirts ourselves. you know.

724
00:46:13.521 --> 00:46:14.897
They're quite bold.

725
00:46:15.398 --> 00:46:17.900
I hope you save them
for the appropriate audience.

726
00:46:18.401 --> 00:46:19.485
and not school.

727
00:46:21.487 --> 00:46:22.989
- Yeah.
- Mm-hmm.

728
00:46:25.783 --> 00:46:26.617
Okay.

729
00:46:28.536 --> 00:46:29.412
Well...

730
00:46:34.333 --> 00:46:36.419
- Don't stay up too late.
- I won't.

731
00:46:38.546 --> 00:46:39.797
- G'night. Love you.
- Good night.

732
00:46:51.976 --> 00:46:53.686
<i>Hey. there.</i>

733
00:46:53.936 --> 00:46:54.812
Hi.

734
00:46:55.980 --> 00:46:58.858
<i>I think there's something wrong
with your camera.</i>

735
00:46:59.900 --> 00:47:02.069
Oh. yeah. it's broken. so...

736
00:47:02.820 --> 00:47:05.031
<i>What's your name. cutie?</i>

737
00:47:05.364 --> 00:47:06.198
Um...

738
00:47:07.241 --> 00:47:09.160
My name is Zach.

739
00:47:10.286 --> 00:47:13.330
<i>Well. hi. Zach.</i>

740
00:47:15.124 --> 00:47:19.420
<i>If I can't see you.
how will I know how big and hard you are?</i>

741
00:47:21.088 --> 00:47:22.173
Um...

742
00:47:22.256 --> 00:47:24.050
Well. I could describe myself.

743
00:47:24.967 --> 00:47:26.719
